$ Oracle: Invisible columns

A → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns can be created to be invisible. The `invisible` keyword must(?) be placed right after the column's → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types[data type]:
code {
create table tq84_tab_with_hidden_col (
    id     integer  generated by default on null as identity,
    num    number,
    txt    varchar2(20),
    ins_dt date           INVISIBLE   default sysdate not null,
    --
    constraint tab_with_hidden_col_pk primary key (id)
);

insert into tq84_tab_with_hidden_col(num, txt) values (42, 'forty-two'  );
insert into tq84_tab_with_hidden_col(num, txt) values (99, 'ninety-nine');
code }

  
By default, invisible columns are not shown when selecting from a table with the star (`*`):
code {
select * from tq84_tab_with_hidden_col;
        ID        NUM TXT                 
---------- ---------- --------------------
         1         42 forty-two           
         2         99 ninety-nine    
code }
         
However, invisible columns can be explicitly specified in the select statement which shows their value:
code {
select
   num,
   txt,
   ins_dt
from
   tq84_tab_with_hidden_col;
   
       NUM TXT                  INS_DT             
---------- -------------------- -------------------
        42 forty-two            2022-02-12 08:43:34
        99 ninety-nine          2022-02-12 08:43:35
code }

  A column can be hidden after the table was created:
code {
alter table tq84_tab_with_hidden_col modify txt invisible;
code }

Cleaning up:
code {
drop table tq84_tab_with_hidden_col;
code }


{ Insert statements

  When inserting values into a hidden column, the column name must be stated. The following example throws
  → development/databases/Oracle/errors/ORA-00913_too-many-values:
code {
create table tq84_ora_00913 (
   vis   integer,
   hid   varchar2(20) invisible
);
 
insert into tq84_ora_00913 values (42, 'hello world');

drop table tq84_ora_00913;
code }

}
{ At least one column must be visible

  Oracle makes sure that each table has at least one visible column (see also → development/databases/Oracle/errors/ORA-54039_table-must-have-at-least-one-column-that-is-not-invisible)

}
{ Views

  It is not possible to hide columns of a → development/databases/Oracle/objects/views - but that wouldn't make sense either.

}

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns/invisible/order[Column order] of invisible columns

  Oracle creates hidden (and → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns/virtual[virtual]) columns for → development/databases/Oracle/objects/indexes/function-based[function based indexes] and → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics/extended.

  The invisible column named `ORA_ARCHIVE_STATE` in → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables[tables] enabled for → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns/in-database-archiving[in-database archiving].
